Package core

Interface HlaExecutionConfigurationManager

  • public interface HlaExecutionConfigurationManager
    Manager used to manage HlaExecutionConfigurations.

    This class is ThreadSafe as defined by Java Concurrency in Practice, see jcip.net.

      • addHlaExecutionConfigurationDefaultInstanceListener

        void addHlaExecutionConfigurationDefaultInstanceListener​(HlaExecutionConfigurationListener listener)
        Add a listener that will automatically be added to all instances of HlaExecutionConfiguration (Both local and remote). The listener is notified when any attribute of an instance of HlaExecutionConfiguration is updated. The listener is also called when an interaction is sent to an instance of HlaExecutionConfiguration. All listeners will automatically be removed when an instance is removed. This method is idempotent.
        Parameters:
        listener - The listener to add.

      • removeHlaExecutionConfigurationDefaultInstanceListener

        void removeHlaExecutionConfigurationDefaultInstanceListener​(HlaExecutionConfigurationListener listener)
        Remove a listener from the set of listeners that are automatically added to new instances of HlaExecutionConfiguration. Note: The listener will not be removed from already existing instances of HlaExecutionConfiguration. This method is idempotent.
        Parameters:
        listener - The listener to remove.

      • addHlaExecutionConfigurationDefaultInstanceValueListener

        void addHlaExecutionConfigurationDefaultInstanceValueListener​(HlaExecutionConfigurationValueListener valueListener)
        Add a valueListener that will automatically be added to all instances of HlaExecutionConfiguration (Both local and remote). The Valuelistener is notified when any attribute of an instance of HlaExecutionConfiguration is updated. Note that the attribute values that are notified are not guaranteed to be the latest available values for that attribute. All listeners will automatically be removed when an instance is removed. This method is idempotent.
        Parameters:
        valueListener - The valueListener to add.

      • removeHlaExecutionConfigurationDefaultInstanceValueListener

        void removeHlaExecutionConfigurationDefaultInstanceValueListener​(HlaExecutionConfigurationValueListener valueListener)
        Remove a valueListener from the set of listeners that are automatically added to new instances of HlaExecutionConfiguration. Note: The valueListener will not be removed from already existing instances of HlaExecutionConfiguration. This method is idempotent.
        Parameters:
        valueListener - The valueListener to remove.

      • setEnabled

        void setEnabled​(boolean enabled)
        Enables or disables the HlaExecutionConfiguration manager. The manager is enabled by default. The state can only be changed when not connected. When the HlaExecutionConfiguration manager is disabled it will act as disconnected, ie throws HlaNotConnectedException.
        Parameters:
        enabled - true to enable the HlaExecutionConfiguration manager, otherwise false

      • setEnabledIfAvailableInFom

        void setEnabledIfAvailableInFom()
        Enables the HlaExecutionConfiguration manager if it is available in the FOM at runtime. The manager is enabled by default. The state can only be changed when not connected. When the HlaExecutionConfiguration manager is disabled it will act as disconnected, ie throws HlaNotConnectedException.

      • isEnabled

        boolean isEnabled()
        Check if the HlaExecutionConfiguration manager is actually enabled when connected. An HlaExecutionConfiguration manager may be disabled with the setEnabled(false) function, or it may be configured as if available in the FOM by the setEnabledIfAvailableInFom() function and then not available in the FOM at runtime.

        This method should only be used when connected, it will always return false when not connected.

        Returns:
        true if connected and the HlaExecutionConfiguration manager is enabled.
